data.description: Remodeled Country Home on 1 Acre +/-     Nothing to do but move in, newer metal roof will practically last forever, newer windows, all new interior kitchen, baths, flooring, painting, many improvements/upgrades throughout.    The 3 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms are all on the main level.   Upstairs is a "finished attic" - a lot of bonus space to use for whatever  you need, and great storage.  The basement is very large and separated into 3 different sections, 1 being the laundry/utility area, a 2nd large room, and then the 3rd large room which has double door access at grade level on the side of the house, currently used as a workshop, motorbike storage, etc.   There is so much storge in the house you won't run out of space.    The garage could accommodate a car, but is mainly used for more storage and workspace and stuff "for the chickens".   The chicken's can convey if you want them, yes seriously!  The garage has stairs to a 2nd level for even more storage.   The yard is mostly flat, easy to mow, great country location close to multiple state parks and all sorts of outdoor activities.   Schools=Wolfsville and Middletown.
